Sentencas: Deposition process of Cr species at the (La, Sr) (Co, Fe)O-3 (LSCF) electrode and Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 (GDC) electrolyte system is investigated under the O-2 reduction conditions in the presence of a Fe-Cr alloy interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Deposition of Cr species at (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Deposition of Cr species preferentially occurs on the surface of the LSCF electrode with and without the cathodic polarization at 900 degrees C, forming SrCrO4 and Cr2O3 phase.
Titulo: Deposition of Cr species at (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At the initial stage of the reaction, Cr deposition was not detected inside the LSCF electrode or at the LSCF electrode/GDC electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Deposition of Cr species at (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Deposition of Cr species on the LSCF electrode surface under the rib of Fe-Cr alloy interconnect is substantial in comparison to that under the channel of the interconnect.
Titulo: Deposition of Cr species at (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate clearly that the deposition of Cr species at the LSCF electrode is essentially a chemical reaction and is kinetically controlled by nucleation reaction between the gaseous Cr species and SrO-enriched/segregated on the LSCF electrode surface.
Titulo: Deposition of Cr species at (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells
